4 §3473. Priority list List of projects; public hearings; final program
5 Each quarter, the The office shall prepare and furnish to the joint committee
6 a prioritized list of qualifying projects based on the applications received by the
7 office. during that quarter. The joint committee shall receive the prioritized list of
8 projects from the office for each of the first three quarters of the year, and shall call
9 a public hearing within thirty days of receiving the list in order to receive public
10 testimony regarding any project on the list. At such hearing, the joint committee
11 shall vote to either accept, reject, or modify the list. Each quarter, the office shall
12 reprioritize the list of projects to reflect the cumulative list of projects recommended
13 by the office. After application recommendations for the last quarter are made by
14 the office, the office shall submit the final waterway dredging and deepening priority
15 program for the ensuing fiscal year to the joint committee for approval. Prior to the
16 convening of the regular session of the legislature, the The joint committee shall hold
17 a public hearing for the purpose of reviewing the final program for the ensuing
18 current fiscal year. Prior to such hearing, the office shall publish the appropriate
19 official notice on the department's website. The final program shall be based upon
20 the anticipated revenues to be appropriated by the legislature or other funding
21 obligation authority and the projects shall be listed in order of priority. Upon review
22 of eligible projects, the joint committee shall establish a list based on the amount
23 appropriated to the program established by the legislature. When this final
24 construction program list is presented to the legislature for funding or funding
25 obligation authority for the ensuing fiscal year, the legislature shall not add any
26 projects to this final construction program. Any project recommended by the office
27 and approved considered by the joint committee for which funds are unavailable in
28 the fiscal year but for which it was approved shall remain on the prioritized list of
29 projects and shall not be removed unless voted on by the joint committee the
30 following year be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
